### Authentication API Tests

### 1. Register new user
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "phone": "0123456789",
  "country": "Vietnam",
  "companyName": "ABC Company",
  "role": "CUSTOMER"
}

### 2. Register admin user
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Admin User",
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "admin123",
  "role": "ADMIN"
}

### 3. Login with email and password
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 4. Login with admin credentials
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### 5. Get current user (replace {token} with actual JWT token)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {token}

### 6. Get user by ID (Admin only - replace {token} with admin JWT token)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/1
Authorization: Bearer {token}

### 7. Test validation - Register with invalid email
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "invalid-email",
  "password": "123"
}

### 8. Test validation - Login with missing password
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com"
}

